---
title: Plant-Based Protein Enchiladas Rojas Protein that tastes like meat (without the meat)
description: Saucy, smothered, hearty, and delicious: This meatless twist on a classic enchilada bake has everything you could possibly want. You’ll make it by wrapping flour tortillas around a filling of spiced ground plant-based protein, then coating the bundles with a healthy glug of salsa roja and a sprinkle of Mexican cheeses. Put it in the oven and let it get piping hot and bubbly, then finish with a spoonful of lime crema and dig into all that deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/plant-based-protein-enchiladas-rojas-2da3000b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plant-based-protein-enchiladas-rojas-5fe122942cb9c84bf5327f07-d5599aa3.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/plant-based-protein-enchiladas-rojas-5fe122942cb9c84bf5327f07
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 10 g
